{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17503744","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17503744"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:06:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:06:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2074"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2074","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2074"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.63,0.09,0.17,0.02,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2074"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102411"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2074","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2074"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2074"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84885"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"3237"},{"type":"tags","id":"4971"},{"type":"tags","id":"11632"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"94"},{"type":"contributions","id":"95"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14674"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35067"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35198"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35199"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42453"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102411","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/102411"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 40-year-old woman presents to her General Practitioner with a twelve month history of sleeping difficulties, specifically reporting difficulty initiating sleep for up to 4 hours. Once asleep, she is then sleeping for only five hours each night and consequently feeling tired throughout the day. She denies nocturia, snoring, or other symptoms that might affect her ability to maintain sleep. She has tried non-pharmacological strategies such as meditation before sleep without success. She is willing to try a medication to help her sleep but does not want to be drowsy the next day as her work requires her to wake up early in the morning. The GP decides to prescribe her a short-course of medication to help with her sleep.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate short-term medication for this patient?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Temazepam","Clonazepam","Diazepam","Flunitrazepam","Trazadone"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis question requires an understanding ion the half-life (i.e. short vs. long acting) of commonly used benzodiazepines. This patient has difficulty initiating sleep but has no issues with the maintenance of sleep. This would make sleep onset insomnia most likely. In this case, the patient may benefit from a short-course of a short-acting benzodiazepine, rather than a long-acting benzodiazepine.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETemazepam\u003C/strong\u003E is a suitable short-acting benzodiazepine as it has a half life of approximately 6 \u2013 12 hours. Longer-acting benzodiazepines such as \u003Cstrong\u003EClonazepam\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003EDiazepam\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003EFlunitrazepam\u003C/strong\u003E have half-lives greater than 24 hours. The longer duration of action of these benzodiazepines may cause impairment of daytime alertness and performance, including ability to drive, which is a safety risk for the patient. Hence, the most suitable choice of benzodiazepine for this woman would be Temazepam.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETrazadone\u003C/strong\u003E is an atypical antidepressant used for major depressive disorder. It has a sedative effect that may be useful to treat insomnia. Whilst available overseas it is not approved for use in Australia and is not available on the PBS. However, a common side effect of trazadone includes daytime drowsiness and therefore is not appropriate for this patient.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Temazepam is a suitable short-acting medication for those with insomnia."],"references":["Griffin C, Kaye A, D P, Bueno F, Kaye A. Benzodiazepine Pharmacology and Central Nervous System\u2013Mediated Effects. Ochsner Journal. 2020;13(2):214-223.","Drug and Alcohol Services South Australia: Benzodiazepines Information for GPs [Internet]. www.sahealth.sa.gov.au/dassa. 2017. Available from: https://www.sahealth.sa.gov.au/wps/wcm/connect/public+content/sa+health+internet/resources/benzodiazepines+information+for+gps"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84885"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2074"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"84885","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/84885"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-12T14:27:14+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-12T14:27:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2074"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102411"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description"